Pattern Recognition

📌 Linked List + Fast & Slow Pointers

Key Observation:

Instead of calculating the length first,
maintain a fixed gap between two pointers.

When the fast pointer reaches the end,

the slow pointer automatically reaches the node immediately before the one that must be removed.

------------------------------------------------------------

Interview Insight

The dummy node is the key trick.
Without it, removing the head requires a separate special case.
With a dummy node, every deletion becomes identical, making the implementation simpler and less error-prone.
